    "text": "My Jewish Learning\nYIDDISH\nThe 10 Best Yiddish Words You’ve Never Heard Of\nThese Yiddish terms aren't widely known, but they're a lot of fun to use.\nJEWISH HUMOR\nAmerican Jewish Humor 101\nWhat's so funny -- and so Jewish?\nJEWISH HISTORY\nSpinoza\nOne of the most significant figures in the history of philosophy, Spinoza was excommunicated by the Jewish community.\nYour Hub for Jewish Education\nDiscover the latest in Jewish events, podcasts and more at the education hub.\nEXPLORE EVENTS\nWHAT'S NEW TODAY\nRECHARGE\nSaying Goodbye to the Greatest Generation\nLike our ancestors in Egypt, we may feel lost without our patriarchs and matriarchs. But a new era is underway.\nGENDER & SEXUALITY\nJudaism and Pornography\nConsumption of adult materials may run afoul of several principles in Jewish law.\nEXPLORE IN DEPTH\nJews and Ukraine: It’s Complicated\nJews have a long and rich history in Ukraine going back more than a millennium. It was once one of ...\nSign Up for My Jewish Learning’s New Shabbat Newsletter\nWelcome to Recharge, a weekly collection of Shabbat readings to refresh your soul. Each Saturday morning we’ll bring you a ...\nSign up for Discovering Jewish Spirituality\nEnhance your Jewish spiritual life with this new email series! “Discovering Jewish Spirituality” will guide you through ways to bring ...\nNEXT TORAH PORTION\nSummary\nIn this Torah portion, Joseph promises Jacob that he will bury him in Canaan. On his deathbed, Jacob blesses his grandchildren, Ephraim and Menashe, and then blesses each of his sons. Jacob dies and is embalmed. Joseph affirms to his brothers that he has forgiven them for their misdeeds. Ending the Book of Genesis, Joseph dies.\nFULL SUMMARY\nHAFTARAH SUMMARY\nParashat Vayechi\nJanuary 07, 2023\nTORAH READING\nGenesis 47:28 - 50:26\nHAFTARAH\nI Kings 2:1 - 2:12\nFEATURED COMMENTARY\nParashat Vayechi: The Legend of You and Me\nJacob’s blessing to his son Joseph offers a potent metaphor about maintaining steadfastness in a world defined by rapid change.\nBY RABBI DEVIN MAIMON VILLARREAL\nFIND SHABBAT CANDLE-LIGHTING TIMES\nVIDEOS\nWEDDINGS & MARRIAGE\nBreaking the Glass at a Jewish Wedding\nWhy the Jewish wedding ceremony ends with a famous bang.\nMOURN\nHow to Have Someone Buried in Israel\nWhat to do if you or a loved one wants a final resting place in an Israeli cemetery.\nHOLOCAUST\nWho Was Anne Frank?\nThe story of the young diarist who became a symbol of the Holocaust.\nRECIPES\nNOSHING\nThe 10 Most Popular Jewish Recipes of 2022\nYou couldn't get enough of these simple, satisfying recipes.\nSEPHARDIC FOOD\nEasy Vegetarian Moroccan Tagine Recipe\nThis all-vegetarian tagine will transport you to Morocco, if only just for dinner.\nCHALLAH\nVegan Turmeric Maple Challah Recipe\nA fluffy, egg-free recipe you will make on repeat.\nMORE FROM MJL\nSAGES & SCHOLARS\nMaimonides’ Medical Writings\nConsidered by many to be the most influential Jewish thinker of all time, Moses Maimonides inspired passionate followers and equally ...\nDENOMINATIONS\nJewish Renewal\nInspired by the visionary leader Rabbi Zalman Schachter-Shalomi, Jewish Renewal describes itself more as an attitude than a denomination.\nSPIRITUALITY\nHow to Have Mindful Sex\nThe secret is not to scratch the itch of desire as soon as it arises.\nBELIEFS & PRACTICES\nJews and Drugs\nWhat does Jewish tradition have to say about the use of recreational drugs?\nPRAYER SERVICES\nSermons in the Synagogue\nRabbinic sermonizing has a long history in Judaism.\nJEWISH HISTORY\nWhat Does It Mean to Be a Rabbi?\nThe traditional rabbinate harks back to ancient practice, but is an evolving institution.\nIgniting journeys of Jewish discovery\nDONATE\nAbout Us\nContact\nAdvertise\nThe Hub\nSpecial Email Series\nLearn Hebrew\nRecharge Newsletter\nWeekly Torah\nShabbat Times\nJewish Calendar\nJewish Recipes\nJewish Prayer\nKaddish Minyan\nDaf Yomi\nNewsletters\nJoin Our Newsletter\nEmpower your Jewish discovery, daily\nSIGN UP\nFollow Us\nFacebook\nTwitter\nYouTube\nInstagram\nThe Nosher\nJTA\nKveller\nNY Jewish Week\nHey Alma\n© 2002-2023 My Jewish Learning. All Rights Reserved Privacy Policy",
